        <h1 class="heading-xlarge">Support</h1>
        <h1 class="heading-large">Support for service teams</h1>
        <p>GOV.UK Verify is built and supported 24/7 by a full-time team at the Government Digital Service.</p>
        <h2 class="heading-medium">Support updates</h2>
        <p>If you have a problem, check for known issues on the <a href="https://verifystatus.digital.cabinet-office.gov.uk">GOV.UK Verify status page</a> first. You can subscribe to get updates whenever GOV.UK Verify creates or updates an incident.</p>
        <h2 class="heading-medium">Support in office hours</h2>
        <p>Our office hours are from 8am to 6pm (GMT), Monday to Friday. Email <a href="mailto:idasupport@digital.cabinet-office.gov.uk">idasupport@digital.cabinet-office.gov.uk</a> to get help and give feedback. The support team aims to respond to questions by the next working day.</p>
        <h2 class="heading-medium">Out-of-hours support</h2>
        <p>We offer 24-hour online support for critical incidents affecting live production services. We have different response times depending on whether the problem you want to report is an emergency.</p>
        <p>It’s only an emergency if:</p>
        <ul class="list list-bullet">
          <li>a significant number of users can’t verify themselves to access your service</li>
          <li>you have reasons to believe there’s been a security breach</li>
          <li>your ‘matching service adapter’ has stopped working</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We’ll reply within 20 minutes and give you hourly updates until the problem’s fixed. We’ll reply by the next working day for any other problems.</p>
